# Platform & Input

**Primary dev target:** Linux desktop. Also support TV form factors (Android TV, tvOS, desktop 10-foot UI).

## Detection

- Use **`platform_detector.dart`** and **`Platform.is*`** — do not assume mobile-only layout.
- TV widgets prefixed `tv_` — focus rails, virtual keyboard, spotlight backgrounds.
- **`Focusable*`** widgets — media cards, list tiles, filter chips for D-pad navigation.

## Desktop (Linux/macOS/Windows)

- **`window_manager`** — title bar, fullscreen via `FullscreenStateManager` / native services.
- **`NativeWindowService`** / **`MacosWindowService`** — platform-specific chrome.
- Keyboard shortcuts and hotkey recorder in settings — preserve existing bindings.

## TV / 10-foot UI

- **`SideNavigationRail`** / **`TvBrowseRail`** — horizontal navigation patterns.
- **`TvVirtualKeyboard`** for text entry on remote-only devices.
- Large touch targets; visible focus indicators — do not rely on hover-only affordances.

## Gamepad

- **`GamepadService`** — map controller input to focus navigation and transport controls.
- Test navigation paths when adding new interactive screens.

## Platform-specific services

| Service | Platform |
|---------|----------|
| `AppleTvRemoteTouchService` | tvOS / Apple TV remote |
| `TvosSystemNavigationService` | tvOS system nav |
| `DiscordRpcService` | Desktop presence |

Gate imports and initialization — dedicated server / headless contexts must not load desktop-only native code on wrong platform.

## Forbidden

- Mouse-only interactions on TV-primary flows
- Hardcoded window sizes ignoring `window_manager` state
- Platform channels without error handling back to Dart
- Breaking Linux focus traversal when adding new overlays/sheets
